HEADWORD: Brigue
<hw>Brigue</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>brigue</ets>, fr. LL. <ets>briga</ets> quarrel. See
<er>Brigand</er>.]</ety> <def>A cabal, intrigue, faction, contention,
strife, or quarrel.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chesterfield.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

